<p>202. The Special Rapporteur remains concerned about the physical and psychological 
integrity of people exercising their rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of 
association in the Islamic Republic of Iran, including the arrest of prominent women human 
rights defenders. He recommends again that the Government put in place an enabling and 
safe environment that is conducive to the free expression of civil society allowing 
individuals to exercise their legitimate freedom of association without undue hindrances. A 
thorough and independent investigation into any allegations of any human rights violations, 
including acts of intimidations or harassments, committed against those exercising their 
rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association, should be conducted; those 
responsible should be held accountable; and victims should be provided with full redress. 
