<p>451. The Special Rapporteur urges once again the authorities to ensure that no individual 
is criminalised for the exercise of his or her legitimate fundamental freedoms. He further 
urges the authorities to take all relevant measures to ensure that any individual and legal 
entity can peacefully exercise their rights of freedom of peaceful assembly and of 
association. He recommends that the Government put in place an enabling and safe 
environment allowing individuals to exercise their legitimate freedoms without undue 
hindrances. A thorough and independent investigation into any allegations of any human 
rights violations, including acts of intimidations or harassments, committed against those 
exercising their rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association, should be 
conducted; those responsible should be held accountable; and victims should be provided 
with full redress. 
